<h2>What Nilea Is (and What It Isn't)</h2>
<p><b>Proactive creator safety</b> begins with a simple observation: for many creators, the hardest part of their work is not creating content. It is living with uncertainty — around who sees it, where it travels, and when it might surface in places that matter personally. Most platforms have safety gaps; their tools enter the situation late, responding after something has already happened with enforcement or takedowns.</p>

<p>Nilea looks earlier. It is a <b>private control space for creators</b>, built around awareness: understanding risk before it becomes an incident, and understanding one's audience before reacting to it.</p>

<p class="pull">This does not mean preventing everything. It means seeing the situation more clearly, so decisions can be made deliberately — not under pressure.</p>

<p>Nilea is not a takedown service or an enforcement platform. It does not decide what should be removed, hidden, or blocked. Instead, it brings signals and findings into one place for review — quietly, without urgency.</p>

<p>Being a creator should not mean losing control over when and how personal exposure happens. Creators decide when their inner circle gets to know. Not content pirates. Not platforms. And not tools acting on their behalf. This is the safety gap Nilea is exploring.</p>
